```

Wait, actually, the `sorry` is not a placeholder in the sense of an unknown set. It's a placeholder in the sense of an unknown element in the structure definition. The actual set expression is `((bt.allPreStates).map (List.toFinset ∘ PreState.forms)).toFinset`.

So we need to prove `List.toFinset (PreState.forms ?m.37 bt ρ) ∈ ((bt.allPreStates).map (List.toFinset ∘ PreState.forms)).toFinset`.

This is true by definition because `((bt.allPreStates).map (List.toFinset ∘ PreState.forms)).toFinset` is the `Finset` of all `List.toFinset (PreState.forms ...)` for all `PreState` `...` in `bt.allPreStates`. Since `ρ` is a `PreState` in `bt.allPreStates`, `List.toFinset (PreState.forms ...)` is indeed an element of that `Finset`.

